<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="span">Avoid Dealer Status</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="1" relname="purpose">to Obtain Capital Gains</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="1003" relname="preparation">Two different groups purchase and sell capital assets :</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="1004" relname="preparation">dealers and investors .</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="1004" relname="joint">Dealers are generally subject to more stringent financial and tax laws and regulations .</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="7" relname="condition">If you are considered a dealer ,</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="1008" relname="span">you will not be able to claim capital gains on , for example , the sale of a property ;</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="1008" relname="elaboration">the sale will be considered business income .</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="1009" relname="span">Capital assets include both securities and real estate .</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="9" relname="elaboration">Of the two , real estate transactions are usually more complex .</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="1011" relname="preparation">Steps</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="1015" relname="span">Decide what you want to do with the property</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="12" relname="elaboration">you own .</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="1018" relname="condition">If you own a house ,</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="1018" relname="contrast">you may want to make improvements</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="1018" relname="contrast">or sell the property .</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="1019" relname="span">Obtaining capital gains</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="1020" relname="span">when you sell the property</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="1021" relname="sequence">may be dependent upon whether you live in the house</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="1022" relname="span">and how long you have owned the house .</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="1024" relname="span">The process</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="21" relname="elaboration">of &quot; flipping &quot; a house ,</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="1025" relname="same_unit">or buying and selling it within a short period of time ,</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="1025" relname="same_unit">may put you in the dealer category .</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="1027" relname="span">The method you use</segment>
<segment id="26" parent="25" relname="purpose">to sell a house could also affect dealer status .</segment>
<segment id="27" parent="1029" relname="span">You might advertise the home as &quot; For Sale By Owner &quot;</segment>
<segment id="28" parent="1030" relname="span">on a sign</segment>
<segment id="29" parent="1031" relname="span">that you place on your front lawn</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="29" relname="purpose">to avoid being seen as a dealer .</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="32" relname="condition">If you advertise in multiple newspapers and on television ,</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="1033" relname="span">you may be seen as a dealer .</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="1035" relname="span">Limit the number of properties</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="33" relname="purpose">you sell .</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="1038" relname="joint">If you own multiple properties</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="1038" relname="joint">and sell and buy properties frequently ,</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="1037" relname="span">the government may view you as a dealer .</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="1040" relname="span">There is an extensive legal case history</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="38" relname="elaboration">that determines the parameters for dealer status .</segment>
<segment id="40" parent="1011" relname="joint">Subdividing a property for the purpose profit could propel you to dealer status .</segment>
<segment id="41" parent="1044" relname="span">Frequency and the extent</segment>
<segment id="42" parent="1045" relname="span">to which you develop a property</segment>
<segment id="43" parent="42" relname="elaboration">to be divided</segment>
<segment id="44" parent="1044" relname="circumstance">also plays a role .</segment>
<segment id="45" parent="1046" relname="sequence">In one case , a person with a non-real-estate job sold several lots of land over a twenty-year period</segment>
<segment id="46" parent="1046" relname="sequence">and obtained capital gains .</segment>
<segment id="47" parent="1049" relname="span">Do n&apos;t set up an office</segment>
<segment id="48" parent="47" relname="elaboration">from which you purchase and sell real property .</segment>
<segment id="49" parent="1051" relname="preparation">Professional real estate agents have offices .</segment>
<segment id="50" parent="51" relname="condition">If you open an office ,</segment>
<segment id="51" parent="1052" relname="span">the government may consider you a dealer .</segment>
<segment id="52" parent="1055" relname="span">Avoid hiring someone</segment>
<segment id="53" parent="52" relname="purpose">to sell your property ,</segment>
<segment id="54" parent="1056" relname="span">as in a person</segment>
<segment id="55" parent="1057" relname="span">over which you have a supervisory role or a person</segment>
<segment id="56" parent="55" relname="elaboration">who you have on a payroll .</segment>
<segment id="57" parent="1059" relname="span">The government may consider this an activity</segment>
<segment id="58" parent="1060" relname="span">consistent with being a real estate professional ,</segment>
<segment id="59" parent="58" relname="elaboration">which would put you in the dealer category .</segment>
<segment id="60" parent="1062" relname="span">Devote only a small portion of your time</segment>
<segment id="61" parent="1063" relname="span">to purchasing and selling property</segment>
<segment id="62" parent="61" relname="purpose">to avoid dealer status .</segment>
<segment id="63" parent="1065" relname="span">If you avoid devoting a significant amount of time</segment>
<segment id="64" parent="63" relname="purpose">to selling a property ,</segment>
<segment id="65" parent="1064" relname="span">the government may not consider you to be a dealer .</segment>
<segment id="66" parent="1067" relname="preparation">Tips</segment>
<segment id="67" parent="1068" relname="span">The factors</segment>
<segment id="68" parent="67" relname="elaboration">that influence dealer status in real estate are evaluated on a case-by-case basis ;</segment>
<segment id="69" parent="1069" relname="joint">no single determinant is more important than another .</segment>
<segment id="70" parent="1069" relname="joint">Avoiding dealer status may help lower your tax rate .</segment>
<segment id="71" parent="1071" relname="span">In the United States , the 2011 tax rate for dealers</segment>
<segment id="72" parent="1072" relname="joint">who sell a property is 35 percent ;</segment>
<segment id="73" parent="1072" relname="joint">those who obtain capital gains are taxed at a rate of 15 percent .</segment>
<segment id="74" parent="1074" relname="preparation">Warnings</segment>
<segment id="75" parent="1075" relname="span">Investors should carefully review the rules</segment>
<segment id="76" parent="75" relname="elaboration">that govern transactions</segment>
<segment id="77" parent="1076" relname="span">involving capital assets</segment>
<segment id="78" parent="77" relname="purpose">to avoid dealer status and associated capital gains issues .</segment>
